## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install nbdev_testing_simon in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure nbdev_testing_simon package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to nbdev_testing_simon
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/Muhammad%20Asif/nbdev_testing_simon):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/Muhammad Asif/nbdev_testing_simon.git
```

or from
[conda](https://anaconda.org/Muhammad%20Asif/nbdev_testing_simon)

``` sh
$ conda install -c Muhammad Asif nbdev_testing_simon
```

or from [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/nbdev_testing_simon/)

``` sh
$ pip install nbdev_testing_simon
```
